   - Static variables are initialized only once, when the class is loaded.

   ```java
public class MyClass {
    public static int myStaticVariable = 10;
}
```

2. **Static Methods**:
   - A static method belongs to the class, not to any instance of the class. It can be called without creating an instance of the class.
   - Static methods can only access static variables and methods.

   ```java
public class MyClass {
    public static int myStaticVariable = 10;
    public static void myStaticMethod() {
        System.out.println(myStaticVariable);
    }
}
```

3. **Static Import**:
